== Initr plugin

Initr automates the lifecycle of computer systems. From provision to operations, puts and keeps the nodes on track. It uses Puppet as enabling technology.

== Installation

=== Adding plugin support to Redmine

To add plugin support to Redmine, install engines plugin:
   See: http://rails-engines.org/

=== Plugin installation

1. Copy the plugin directory into the vendor/plugins directory

2. Migrate plugin:
   rake db:migrate_plugins

3. Edit application's config/routes.rb and paste lines from plugin's routes.rb

4. Configure puppet_production database at application's config/database.yml

5. Start Redmine

Installed plugins are listed on 'Admin -> Information' screen.

=== Initr plugins installation ===

1. copy or soft link initr plugin directory to redmine vendor/plugins directory

2. execute migrations:
   rake db:migrate_plugins
